      <p>The 4-4-6 breathing pattern — a form of slow-paced, controlled breathing — activates the parasympathetic nervous system, which research shows can help reduce physiological markers of stress including heart rate and cortisol. Studies published in journals including <em>Frontiers in Psychology</em> support its use as an accessible, evidence-informed tool for stress and anxiety relief.</p>
