  <div class="faq-list">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What does "evidence-based" actually mean on Bloomwell? <span class="faq-arrow">▾</span></div>
      <div class="faq-answer">It means every practice on Bloomwell is grounded in peer-reviewed clinical or psychological research — not trends, personal anecdotes, or marketing. We draw on established frameworks: Mindfulness-Based Stress Reduction (MBSR) for meditation and breathwork; Cognitive Behavioural Therapy (CBT) principles for thought-based practices; Positive Psychology research (Dr Martin Seligman) for gratitude and journaling; Acceptance & Commitment Therapy (ACT) for values work; exercise physiology for movement; and the Harvard Healthy Eating Plate and WHO dietary guidelines for nutrition. We make only claims that research supports — and we never overstate certainty where evidence is still emerging.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is Bloomwell suitable for complete beginners? <span class="faq-arrow">▾</span></div>
      <div class="faq-answer">Absolutely — Bloomwell was built with beginners in mind first. Every practice uses plain language, step-by-step guidance, and no prior experience is needed. We meet you exactly where you are, whether this is your very first meditation or your hundredth.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is this a replacement for professional medical or mental health care? <span class="faq-arrow">▾</span></div>
      <div class="faq-answer">No — and we want to be completely clear about this. Bloomwell provides general wellness information and practices to support everyday wellbeing. It is not a substitute for medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. If you are experiencing a mental or physical health condition, please consult a qualified professional. In a crisis, please call 988 (US) immediately.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much time do I need each day to see a benefit? <span class="faq-arrow">▾</span></div>
      <div class="faq-answer">As little as 5 minutes can make a real difference. Our shortest practice — the Morning Breath Reset — takes just 5 minutes. We firmly believe that small, consistent acts of self-care compound into meaningful change over time. You don't need to do a lot. You just need to show up regularly. Start tiny.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is my personal and health information kept private? <span class="faq-arrow">▾</span></div>
